 Others of you, you'll be praying, "God, I care more about what other people think of me."

540
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:10,000
 As I sat in Psalm 42 and God spoke to me out of His Word, it was my inner voice was so very loud.

541
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:22,000
 It was so very defeating, but it was only when Christ's voice by His Spirit through His truth began to speak

542
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:34,000
 that the defeating voice was defeated, that a victorious voice actually spoke instead, and it changed my life forever.

543
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:42,000
 I found hope in that place, not because of anything I had to offer, but because of everything that Jesus had to give.

544
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:48,000
 So if you're here, you need to know you have a reason to hope in God.

545
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:56,000
 That if you don't feel good enough, you don't need to stroke your ego to make yourself feel better, because the reality is,

546
00:41:56,000 --> 00:42:03,000
 no one was good enough. All of us, like sinners, had gone astray.

547
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:11,000
 We were enemies of God, not His children. No one was good. No one was righteous. No, not one.

548
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:18,000
 And yet Christ, He stepped in and He became good on our behalf. He did what we could not.

549
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:25,000
 If it's, "I feel too far gone," then you don't need to coddle your emotions and tell yourself something wrong,

550
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:31,000
 tell yourself something untrue. You need to understand, yes, you were too far gone, for we all were too far gone.

551
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:37,000
 And yet no one was outside the reach of God's long stretched arm.

552
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:45,000
 For Christ would go as far as was necessary to save anyone that would place their faith in Him.

553
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:49,000
 For some of you, you feel like you're just a burden. Here's the thing.

554
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:57,000
 You don't have to fool yourself into feeling differently, because we all were a burden.

555
00:42:57,000 --> 00:43:04,000
 No one had anything good to offer God. No one had any value to bring to the table.

556
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:11,000
 And yet Christ stepped into our story and He offered everything that we could not.

557
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:17,000
 This is the gospel. You may feel hopeless, for we all were hopeless.

558
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:24,000
 And yet for those that believe Jesus Christ is the Son of God, sent to save the world,

559
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:29,000
 for all who would place their faith in Him, then you can go from hopelessness to hope.

560
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:37,000
 You can move from depression into prosperity. You can believe, I can have life and have life eternally.

561
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:40,000
 Let me pray that you would believe that true for yourself tonight.

562
00:43:40,000 --> 00:43:49,000
 Jesus, we know we have reason to hope, for in you we see one who has granted us salvation.

563
00:43:49,000 --> 00:43:54,000
 I pray, God, please here tonight for these friends in this room,

564
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:59,000
 I'm asking you, would you work in a way that doesn't just change what we know?

565
00:43:59,000 --> 00:44:04,000
 God, so many Christians are, they're content to just learn more, change what they understand.

566
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:10,000
 But God, we don't want to just change what we know. We want to be changed at who we are.

567
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:15,000
 We want to be different, God. And for my friends here tonight that are struggling with depression,

568
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:21,000
 and I don't know where on that range they fall, whether they see themselves as just generally sad,

569
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:29,000
 or if they find themselves truly despondent, God, I pray here tonight, would you liberate them?

570
00:44:29,000 --> 00:44:33,000
 Would they, as we go into this final song, would they speak to their soul?

571
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:38,000
 Would they say, "Why are you so downcast?"

572
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:45,000
 Hope in God, for I have good reason to hope. Not because of anything I have to give,

573
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:52,000
 not because of anything that I've ever done, but because of all that Christ has given, and all that Jesus has done.

574
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:59,000
 I have reason to hope. I will not suppress my feelings. I will fill them in full.

575
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:08,000
 And yet I will bring all of that emotion to the cross, because it's there that everything can be changed.

576
00:45:08,000 --> 00:45:15,000
 Please, God, do that now. There are some here that do not know you. Save them, please, God.

577
00:45:15,000 --> 00:45:21,000
 There are some here who, as I'm praying, they're thinking about what's next.

578
00:45:21,000 --> 00:45:26,000
 They're wanting to figure out the rest of their evening. They've already discounted this next song,

579
00:45:26,000 --> 00:45:30,000
 but you, God, have not counted them out yet. You have something even still for them.

580
00:45:30,000 --> 00:45:35,000
 There are others, God, that they feel like they're in an amazing spot tonight.

581
00:45:35,000 --> 00:45:42,000
 And Lord, they get to rejoice at the fact that you, Jesus, have given them this situation.

582
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:47,000
 And yet they also can take heart, because they know, though the clouds are always moving,

583
00:45:47,000 --> 00:45:51,000
 the sun above is always shining, my Jesus sits enthroned forever.

584
00:45:51,000 --> 00:45:57,000
 God, we pray, meet with us here. We want to be more like you.

585
00:45:57,000 --> 00:46:02,000
 And so would you do that in us, please, we pray, in Christ's name. Amen.

586
00:46:02,000 --> 00:46:12,000
 [BLANK_AUDIO]

